# Baseline vs Advanced Model Comparison Plan

## Background

The current model (`train_v4_robust.py`) achieves **98.11% accuracy** using many advanced techniques. To demonstrate the value of these techniques in an FYP context, we need a **baseline model** that uses the same architecture (EfficientNetB0) but **without any advanced methods**, trained on the **same BHD dataset** (Bleached/Healthy/Dead coral — 720/712/150 images).

---

## What the Current Advanced Model Uses (to be REMOVED in baseline)

| Advanced Technique | Current Model | Baseline Model |
|---|---|---|
| 5-Seed Ensemble | ✅ Seeds [42–46] | ❌ Single seed (42) |
| Stochastic Weight Averaging (SWA) | ✅ Last 5 epochs | ❌ None |
| Test-Time Augmentation (TTA) | ✅ Multi-scale + flip | ❌ None |
| Mixup Data Augmentation | ✅ Alpha=0.1 | ❌ None |
| Hard Example Oversampling | ✅ 20–30× for specific images | ❌ None |
| Label Smoothing | ✅ 0.05 | ❌ None (0.0) |
| Cosine Decay LR Schedule | ✅ Custom | ❌ Fixed LR / ReduceLROnPlateau |
| Environmental Color Jitter | ✅ Hue + Saturation | ❌ None |
| L2 Regularization | ✅ 0.0002 | ❌ None |
| Dead Class Weight Boost | ✅ 1.3× multiplier | ❌ Standard balanced weights only |
| Fine-Tuning Strategy | ✅ Unfreeze last 100 layers | ❌ Freeze all base, train head only |
| Grad-CAM | ✅ Eigen Smooth + Aug Smooth | ❌ Standard Grad-CAM only |

---

## Comparison Indicators

We will compare both models on the following metrics, all evaluated on the **same test set** (same split seed = 42):

### 1. Overall Performance
| Metric | Description |
|---|---|
| **Test Accuracy** | Overall % correct predictions |
| **Macro-Averaged Precision** | Unweighted mean precision across 3 classes |
| **Macro-Averaged Recall** | Unweighted mean recall across 3 classes |
| **Macro-Averaged F1-Score** | Harmonic mean of macro precision & recall |
| **Weighted-Averaged F1-Score** | F1 weighted by class support |

### 2. Per-Class Performance
| Metric | Description |
|---|---|
| **Per-Class Precision** | Precision for Healthy, Bleached, Dead |
| **Per-Class Recall** | Recall for Healthy, Bleached, Dead |
| **Per-Class F1-Score** | F1 for each class |
| **Dead Class Performance** | Particularly important — Dead has only 15 test samples |

### 3. Confusion Matrix
- Side-by-side confusion matrices to visualize misclassification patterns

### 4. Training Dynamics
| Metric | Description |
|---|---|
| **Training Accuracy Curve** | Learning speed comparison |
| **Validation Accuracy Curve** | Generalization comparison |
| **Training Loss Curve** | Convergence comparison |
| **Validation Loss Curve** | Overfitting comparison |
| **Train-Val Gap** | Overfitting indicator |

### 5. Grad-CAM Interpretability
| Metric | Description |
|---|---|
| **Standard Grad-CAM Heatmaps** | Visual comparison of what the model "looks at" |
| **Focus Quality** | Whether the model attends to coral vs background |

### 6. Model Complexity
| Metric | Description |
|---|---|
| **Number of Trainable Parameters** | How many params are updated during training |
| **Training Time** | Total wall-clock time |
| **Inference Time (per image)** | Speed of single-image prediction |

