### [NEW] `05_Baseline_Model/train_baseline.py`

A simplified EfficientNetB0 training script with these characteristics:

- **Architecture**: EfficientNetB0 with `include_top=False` + GlobalAveragePooling2D + Dense(3, softmax)
- **Transfer Learning**: Freeze ALL EfficientNetB0 layers, train only the classification head
- **No Dropout**: No dropout layer (simplest possible head)
- **Optimizer**: Adam with fixed learning rate (1e-4)
- **Loss**: Standard `CategoricalCrossentropy` (no label smoothing)
- **Data Augmentation**: Basic only — horizontal flip, rotation (±15°), zoom (±10%)
- **No Mixup**, no color jitter, no hard example oversampling
- **Class Weights**: Standard `sklearn balanced` weights (no manual boosting)
- **Callbacks**: ModelCheckpoint (save best val_accuracy) + EarlyStopping (patience=5)
- **No Ensemble**: Single model, single seed (42)
- **Evaluation**: Direct `model.predict()` — no TTA
- **Data Split**: Same split seed (42) and same 80/10/10 ratio to ensure identical test set
- **Grad-CAM**: Standard Grad-CAM (no eigen_smooth, no aug_smooth)

The script will also save:
- Training history (JSON + PNG plot)
- Classification report (TXT + PNG)
- Confusion matrix (PNG)
- Grad-CAM samples (PNG)
- Model summary with param counts (TXT)
- Inference time measurement

