## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Epochs**: The advanced model trains for 30 epochs. Should the baseline also train for 30 epochs, or use EarlyStopping to stop sooner? I'm proposing EarlyStopping with patience=5 (more typical for a baseline approach), but can match 30 if you prefer consistency.

> [!NOTE]
> **Data Augmentation**: The baseline uses only basic augmentation (flip, rotation, zoom). The current model additionally uses brightness jitter, shear, and environmental color jitter. This is intentional — the baseline should represent a "standard" approach without domain-specific tricks.
